        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A severe form of citrullinemia type 1 characterized biologically by hyperammonemia and clinically by progressive lethargy poor feeding and vomiting seizures and possible loss of consciousness within one to a few days of birth with variable signs of increased intracranial pressure. The condition can lead to significant neurologic deficits."
